curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/2021' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM3715", "table_name": "APPLICATION INFORMATION", "content": "APPLICATION INFORMATION  The combination of Speaker and Receiver is always used in portable devices, and high voltage class D speaker  driver is used to drive speaker in order to provide high audio volume. But the high output voltage of class D speaker  driver will damage the receiver driver. The SGM3715 provides the safe isolation between receiver driver and high  voltage class D speaker driver. The SGM3715 provides low RON channels to pass the positive and negative signals  from capless receiver driver. The circuit is shown in Figure 1.   VCC IN1 IN2 COM1 COM2 NO1 NC1 NO2 NC2 GND VCC (2.7V ~ 12V) R1 10Ω VCC C 0.1μF Capless Receiver Driver Control R4 + - 10μF R2 1kΩ R3 1kΩ Speaker + Receiver High Voltage Class D Speaker Driver Audio Signal EN 1kΩ VCC (2.7V ~ 12V) PVSS CN CP 0.1μF 0.1μF R5 1kΩ D1 R6 12Ω R7 12Ω SGM3715     Figure 1. Typical Application Circuit for Speaker + Receiver             0.8Ω, High Voltage, Rail-to-Rail Negative  SGM3715  Signal Passing, Dual, SPDT Analog Switch      12  NOVEMBER 2017  SG Micro Corp  www.sg-micro.com  APPLICATION INFORMATION (continued)  In order to improve audio performance of portable equipment, external speaker power amplifier is always selected to  replace the internal integrated speaker power amplifier. Because the audio signal quality of audio line out or headset  driver is better than that of the integrated speaker power amplifier, the audio signal of line out or headset driver is  selected as the high performance audio signal source for external speaker power amplifier. High performance  SGM3715 is used as the 1-to-2 HiFi signal switch in this application. The circuit is shown in Figure 2, and a stable  3.3V power supply is required in this circuit.       VCC IN1 IN2 COM1 COM2 NO1 NC1 NO2 NC2 GND VCC = 3.3V R1 10Ω C 0.1μF Audio Line Out or Headset Driver Control R4 + - 10μF Speaker 2 High Voltage Class D Speaker Driver EN 1kΩ VCC (2.7V ~ 12V) PVSS CN CP 0.1μF 0.1μF R5 1kΩ R R L L R + - 10μF VCC (2.7V ~ 12V) Headset Speaker 1 L SGM3715     Figure 2. Typical Application Circuit for 1-to-2 HiFi Audio Signal Switch                        "}'
